INSERT INTO `mmi_faq_master` VALUES (1,'How to choose an insurance for your vehicle?','Why insurance is necessary for your vehicle?','Offers financial protection in the event of a mishap – Insurance protects owner of the vehicle against damages to the vehicle. Takes care of third party liability arising due to damages suffered by a third party for death or injury and also for property of third party. Mandatory by law- Any vehicle running on Indian roads has to have motor insurance, especially third-party liability cover. Not having insurance cover can led to a severe penalty, as per new rule the fine will be Rs.2,000/- and/or imprisonment of up to 3 months. If continue to drive a vehicle without insurance then liable to pay a fine of Rs.4,000 and/or imprisonment of up to 3 months.','1','2025-10-16 11:33:30',NULL,'2025-10-18 06:10:33',NULL),(2,'How to choose an insurance for your vehicle?','Types of motor insurance?','There are two types of motor insurances: 1. Third-party liability insurance-  Called as Liability Only Policy or earlier called as Act Only Liability Policy This type of insurance policy is mandated by law for all motor vehicles plying on the roads. This insurance provides cover to third-party liability for damages to property of third party as well as for bodily injuries or death of persons. Third-party liability insurance only covers minimal risks as required and compulsory as per law and it does not protect the policyholder from damage or theft of the insured vehicle. 2. Comprehensive motor insurance- It often referred to as a package policy, as it includes third-party liability cover and the expenses incurred by the policyholder in the event of damage or theft of the insured vehicle. The comprehensive insurance policy can be enhanced through add-on covers that offer extended benefits.','1','2025-10-16 11:33:30',NULL,'2025-10-18 06:10:33',NULL),(3,'How to choose an insurance for your vehicle?','Different kinds of add-ons?','1. Zero depreciation cover- It is also referred as nil depreciation cover or bumper to bumper policy. It offers full claim on the value of parts replaced due to accident without any deduction for depreciation. 2. Engine protection cover- It will cover the consequential damage to the internal parts of the engine arising out of water ingression or out of leakage of lubricating oil due to an accident. 3. Consumables cover- Components that are used in a vehicle such as nuts and bolts, screen washers, engine oil, etc. are collectively referred to as consumables. The insurance company does not bear the cost of these components at the time of a claim, with this add on cover customer will receive coverage for consumables. 4. Return to Invoice (RTI) cover- In case of a Total Loss / Constructive Total Loss or Theft it covers the gap between the Insured Declared Value and the Invoice Value for purchasing a new vehicle of same make & model along with the registration and other applicable taxes. 5. Key replacement cover- It covers expenses arising out of replacing the keys and the cost of repair the lock-set in case the keys have be stolen, lost or damaged. 6. EMI cover- It covers the Equated Monthly Installment payable by the insured to financial institution as mentioned in the policy schedule (No. of EMI) for the period insured vehicle is in garage for repair, provided insured vehicle is damaged by a covered peril. 7. Loss of personal belongings cover- Loss of electronic equipment’s, laptops, etc. kept in the insured vehicle is offered coverage under this add-on insurance plan. 8. No Claim Bonus (NCB) protect cover- The NCB protector protects customers earned No Claim Bonus, in the event of own damage claim made for partial loss, like vehicle was in parked condition and windshield got damaged due to external means will cover and the NCB also retain for the next policy renewal. 9. Roadside assistance cover- This add-on cover offers 24/7 protection to the policyholder from incidents such as flat tyre, fuel depletion, requirement for expert scrutiny, etc. 10. Daily allowance cover- This add-on cover offers reimbursement for the expenses involved in hiring an alternate vehicle when the insured automobile is undergoing repairs at a garage.','1','2025-10-16 11:33:30',NULL,'2025-10-18 06:10:33',NULL),(4,'How to choose an insurance for your vehicle?','What are covered and what are the conditions for it?','Motor Insurance covers: The main components of motor insurance are liability coverage; this insurance provides protection to third-parties for damages to property or bodily injuries to persons, where the policyholder is accountable for the accident. The damages to the vehicle due to the following perils are usually covered under Own Damage (OD) section of the Motor Insurance policy: a) Fire, Explosion, Self- Ignition, Lightning b) Burglary/Housebreaking / Theft c) Riot & Strike d) Earthquake e) Flood, Storm, Cyclone, Hurricane, tempest, inundation, hailstorm, frost f) Accidental external means g) Malicious Act h) While in Transit by Rail/ Road, Inland waterways, Lift, Elevator or Air i) Land slide / Rock slide. Motor Insurance excludes: The following contingencies are usually excluded under the Motor Insurance Policy: a) Not having a valid and effective Driving License as required by law b) While Vehicle is used for unlawful purposes and for usage not intended as per registration certificate c) Wear and Tear/ Electrical or Mechanical Breakdowns. d) Consequential losses or damages which are consequence of a certain action resulting by the policyholder or a third-party (whether intentional or by accident) and not an outcome of an uncertain event are not covered. For instance, tyre and rim damages may lead to entire suspension assembly damage which was not directly affected in the incident but it rise due to driving vehicle to the extent knowingly.','1','2025-10-16 11:33:30',NULL,'2025-10-18 06:10:33',NULL),(5,'How to choose an insurance for your vehicle?','Claim process for Personal & commercial vehicles?','The same claim process will be followed for personal and commercial vehicle. In commercial vehicle some additional documents require to submit like Fitness Certificate, Permit, Etc. Claim process for Accidental Loss: In case of reimbursement customer can make the full payment to the workshop and take the vehicle and the amount will be reimbursed in his account basis the terms and conditions of the policy. Claim Process for Total Theft.','1','2025-10-16 11:33:30',NULL,'2025-10-18 06:10:33',NULL),(6,'How to choose an insurance for your vehicle?','What process is to follow at the time of third party (Injuries/Death/Property Damage) claim arises?','1. At the time of third party claim the customer and party have to report and register an FIR in a nearby police station. 2. Immediately inform insurer in advance regarding there being any death or injury or damage to property of third party. 3. Submit a copy of notice received form the party along with require documents to the insurance company in response of that insured will get a lawyer appointed by them.','1','2025-10-16 11:33:30',NULL,'2025-10-18 06:10:33',NULL),(7,'How to choose an insurance for your vehicle?','How to claim in case of death of owner/passenger/driver?','1. Intimate the insurer about the incidence and resulting loss. 2. Ask for an FIR followed by Final Report from nearby police station. It will be one of the most important documents needed for processing the claim. 3. Complete the formalities with the insurer that includes filling the claim form, provide photographs of the car accident (if any). 4. Submit all the requisite documents with insurance company to verify the details. 5. In the eventuality of death of the owner-driver, the nominee shall file the claim. She/he will be awarded the claim amount as per the policy.','1','2025-10-16 11:33:30',NULL,'2025-10-18 06:10:33',NULL),(8,'How to choose an insurance for your vehicle?','Why to take insurance from Dealership?','1. Entire process of insurance purchase is streamline and more convenient when it done through a dealership 2. Multiple choice of insurance companies are available with dealers 3. Dealer can help to choose right insurance and add on products as per customer’s requirement. 4. Dealers have a separate helpdesk for insurance queries and end to end claim assistance that will help at the time of need to the customer 5. Near cashless facility available at dealer where customer can get hassle free claim service and he need not to pay repair charges in full to the workshop 6. Standard repair process laid by manufacturer towards safety measures are being followed by the dealers for vehicle repairing assures good quality of service. 7. Customer need not to worry on fitment of genuine parts during repair progress','1','2025-10-16 11:33:30',NULL,'2025-10-18 06:10:33',NULL),(9,'How to choose an insurance for your vehicle?','Is it really cashless?','Cashless facility means where the insurer pays its liability directly to workshop and where the insured has to pay the remaining amount to workshop which are not covered under the standard policy such as the deprecation amount, consumable, policy excess and salvage.','1','2025-10-16 11:33:30',NULL,'2025-10-18 06:10:33',NULL),(10,'How to choose an insurance for your vehicle?','Filling a correct nominee name is how much important?','It is very important to mention nominee name in the motor insurance policy as in the eventuality of death of the owner-driver, the nominee will file the claim. She/he will be awarded the claim amount as per the policy.','1','2025-10-16 11:33:30',NULL,'2025-10-18 06:10:33',NULL);
/*!40000 ALTER TABLE `mmi_faq_master` ENABLE KEYS */;
UNLOCK TABLES;

